This paper deals with the problem of mining association rules, which is a well-studied topic in the field of databases (cs.DB). The paper proposes an algorithm for generating concise and complete representations of association rules, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the mathematical validation of the algorithm, which involves concepts from discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper applies the algorithm to an existing basis of association rules, which involves techniques from information retrieval (cs.IR).
